User submissions
On May 19, the well-known academic information public account "Aizhi Scholar" published a recruitment notice for Xiaoguo Culture, recruiting positions such as party affairs director, government relations manager, and public opinion specialist. The article was deleted a few minutes later.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Netizen contribution
"But the people don't agree"
On May 19, it was reported that the "Korean restriction order" that had been implemented for eight years was about to be lifted, and many Korean stars were about to go to China to participate in activities.
This move was strongly resisted by netizens. A large number of netizens called for collective reporting to the relevant departments online and shared reporting strategies and screenshots. No Korean star will be allowed to come to China to make money.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
Later, Yakushiji issued an announcement that subsequent performances in China were also cancelled.
According to netizens, the real reason for the cancellation was related to "religion"

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On May 19, Zhejiang's government service website reported that six men participated in a homosexual party. However, some netizens found that a larger-scale homosexual party was made public ten days ago, but it was not reported. They questioned Zhejiang's selective reporting.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: Netizens corrected that the number was sixteen instead of ten ten days ago.
